<br>
You need to get &quot;a storm giant head&quot; from any of the base giants in the zone. They drop this fairly commonly. <br>
<br>
Hand in the head to Askr, and when he asks if it was you who tore the head from it's previous owner, say &quot;it was me&quot;. You'll need to tell Askr to continue a few times. He'll then give you a 4 slot container, which he'd like you to fill with 1 item from each giant tribe. <br>
<br>
The Ocean Giants drop a beard semi-commonly, you need one of these. <br>
The Desert Giants drop a bone semi-rarely, you'll need one of these as well. <br>
The Forect Giants drop a sash semi-commeonly. <br>
<br>
Take these 3 items, combine them in the container Askr gave you, and hand him the result. <br>
<br>
Askr will then tell you about bastion of thunder, ask him &quot;what bastion of thunder&quot;, and he'll give you another container. <br>
<br>
In each of the 3 giant camps, there are named giants. These named giants can drop spectral and ethereal parchments, various mediocre loot, and they'll drop 3 Esoteric Medallions on death. You need to get any two different Medallions. (They're all named the same, but identify as west, south and north). <br>
<br>
Take your two medallions, and combine then in the container that Askr gave you to result in the Esoteric Meld. Hand this in to Askr for the character flag to enter Bastion of Thunder. <br>
<br>
The first time you zone into Bastion of Thunder you need to use the zone-line in the plane of Storms. (It's in the center area, with the Tempest Toads, and the Hurricane). Just put invisibility up, and click on the small shrine in the middle. Once you do this, you'll be able to use the zoneline in Tranquility. <br>
<br>
The quest takes about 1 to 2 groups, and will take a single person about 1 or 2 days to collect all the pieces. <br>
<br>
The reward for this quest is the flag for entry to Torden, Bastion of Thunder, and home of Karana. <br>
